 The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission has filed a 14-count charge bordering on alleged money laundering and other related offences against suspected Internet fraudster, Ismaila Mustapha, also known as Mompha. Mompha will be arraigned before Justice Mohammad Liman of the Federal High Court, Ikoyi, Lagos, on Monday, November 25. He will be prosecuted by EFCC counsel, Mr Rotimi Oyedepo. Mompha filed a N5m suit against the commission on Thursday for alleged illegal detention.